President Obama has declared a major disaster in the District of Columbia due to severe winter storms and snowstorms that occurred from February 5-11, 2010. This declaration allows for federal aid to supplement the District's recovery efforts. Federal funding is available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, emergency protective measures, and hazard mitigation measures. Regis Leo Phelan has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area. Additional designations may be made if requested by the District of Columbia and further damage assessments warrant it. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.